FBIS3-54713 "drsov001_s_94012" FBIS-SOV-94-001 Document Type:Daily Report 3 Jan 1994 Georgia Interpol National Center Head Appointed LD3112103093 Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network in Georgian 0300 GMT 31 Dec 93 LD3112103093 Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network Language: Georgian Article Type:BFN [Text] The Georgian Internal Affairs Ministry has become a member of Interpol. By Georgian Interior Minister Shota Kviraia's order, Police Major Giorgiy Aleksidze has been appointed the head of the Georgian Bureau of Interpol National Center. Giorgiy Aleksidze was born in 1962. He graduated from Tbilisi State University. He has held the office of the head of a department in the Georgian Security Ministry. He has a perfect command of the French and English languages.
